    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've developed after thoroughly reading all relevant source files:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Public Namespace\n\n**6 files to touch, following the exact same pattern as `Bun.TOML` / `Bun.YAML` / `Bun.JSON5`:**\n\n### 1. CREATE `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\n- `create()` builds a JS object with both `parse` and `stringify`\n- **`parse`** directly reuses `bun.ini.Parser` (already exported from `src/bun.zig` line 230 as `pub const ini = @import(\"./ini.zig\")`), mirroring the existing `IniTestingAPIs.parse` in ini.zig exactly\n- **`stringify`** is self-contained: emit top-level primitives as `key = value`, then top-level objects as `[section]` headers — built with `wtf.StringBuilder` and `jsc.JSPropertyIterator`\n\n### 2. `src/bun.js/api.zig` — add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n\n### 3. `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` — 4 additions:\n- Lazy property constant alongside TOML/YAML/JSON5 (~line 70)\n- `@export` alongside other format exports (~line 140)\n- `getINIObject` getter function (after `getYAMLObject`, ~line 1289)\n- `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;` import constant (~line 2083)\n\n### 4. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` — add `macro(INI) \\` before `macro(JSON5)` (alphabetical)\n\n### 5. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` — add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `bunObjectTable` before `JSONC`\n\n### 6. `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` — add `namespace INI` with full JSDoc for both `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string`, inserted after the `TOML` namespace block",
